				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">hmm, joggin the ol memory lose here, lets see... (not in any particular order, just in order that i remember them)
<br />

<br />
1) manastone (quickly removed from drop table, but left in game) effect on current game, great for pling lowbies, twinks.
<br />
2) complete heal, nuff said
<br />
3) donals bp (clicky effect  of CH w/ 30 sec casting time) later changed (or nerfed depending on point of view)
<br />
4) modrods nuff said
<br />
5) charm (debateable)
<br />
6) slows, this has to be the single most unballanceing spell in the game, no matter who gets it, cause seems that sony has to ballance all content on the existance of slow spells / effects.  Thus any group with out slow would be unable to do anything effectively / efficiently.  would they fix this? no, this would require them to retune every encounter from oldworld stuff to god.
<br />

<br />
just some thoughts on class ballance to strike up some discussion.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
