				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A group or two of SK with iHT would achieve the same, and yet that has never been too powerful to nerf. Nowadays 2 non-crit nukes would do the same dmg as manaburn.
<br />

<br />
What made wizards so effective was that they could all insta-port to a not very hard to get to (often outdoor) named. 'Team HT' would all have to find ports. Plus SKs have always been a little rarer than wizards.
<br />

<br />
So MB definitely was a game-disrupting ability but it was an unfortunate combination of factors. If mages had got MB instead of wizards, for example, it probably would never have ended up being nerfed - just slowly made irrelevant, as with most aa. [although admittedly it had to be capped else it would be a MONSTER nuke today]
<br />

<br />
Over the course of the game, probably slow has had the most unbalancing effect; with CH pretty close behind. Charm has to have an honourable mention too, though it has received lots of nerfs over the years.
<br />

<br />
Most imbalances have been blunted with mudflation - eg. CH will no longer be the best hp/s spell after the next expansion. Slow is being mitigated. Manapools and manaregen are already big enough to make Donal's BP fairly pointless even if it started dropping again - most clerics could cast a CH every 30 sec indefinitely anyway.
<br />

<br />
But manastones? They would have totally destroyed the game as we know it. They had to go.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
