			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'd have to say CH is still on top of the list.  It's a level 39 spell, yet still one of the most powerful spells in the game.  It should never have been designed the way it is. 
<br />

<br />
Obviously any system that creates unlimited mana (manastones, pre-nerf mod rods) is eventually going to need nerfing.
<br />

<br />
SLOW is becoming the next big obstacle.  As said above, every encounter has to be balanced around the fact you can slow.  They had to make special codings for mobs that are immune to slow, or mitigate slows, etc. in order to make things work for the future. 
<br />

<br />
Becasue everything must be balanced according to HAVING slow, anybody with a group that does NOT have slow is virtually assured of failure in the newer expansions.   It has become a manadatory need, and anything that becomes absolutely mandatory for a group to survive is obviously on the brink of being "overpowered". 
<br />

<br />
If things like slows and CH did not exist, many encounters would be re-balanced in substantially different ways and allow a wider variety of group make-ups.<br />_________________<br /><DIV *****"position:relative; width=80%; filter:glow(color=FF0000)"><a *****"font-weight:bold; color:#FFFFFF; text-decoration: none" href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796  target="new-window"><b>Lord Zacatac Soulwanderer</b></a></div>"1450 Club" Tradeskiller
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">All I want for Christmas is /PET AE-TAUNT.</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
