			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">1. Charm
<br />

<br />
Far and away the leader. Charm needs a solid down-size. TD3 means almost safe pets, and almost-safe pets that hit for 1k when real pet classes get pets that don't even hit for 100 is crazy.
<br />

<br />
2. Slow
<br />

<br />
This would have been fine had it been low values, like 20%. But once the game had 75% slows, it was always going to mean either balancing for having/not having slow impossible.
<br />

<br />
The other entires do not even register compared to those two.
<br />

<br />
Manastones are not a balance issue as they are today, they are too rare, and too limited in places they can be used.
<br />

<br />
Manaburn is not a balance is as it is today, it's just the top of the pile for instant one-off DPS (in exchange for poor DPM).
<br />

<br />
CH is no way a balance issue as it is today, its just a 10second 7500 heal, and in many places nowadays, eg Tipt, it isn't the no-brainer it used to be compared to Holy Light - I play cleric at 65/300+AAs too, I know (but back in the day, it was heavily imbalancing).
<br />

<br />
Mod rods are not a balance issue as they are today either, but let's not open that one. <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="razz" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Suzanna.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
