				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">1) Charm - Not much needs to be said. It could easily be remedied by significantly weakening the charmed monster.
<br />

<br />
2) Slow - The only spell in the game that's required for nearly everything you do. The most powerful slow in the game should be for no more then 30%.
<br />

<br />
3) Manastones - Everything that's instant cast and not a buff is overpowered. They would be considerably less powerful if they had a cast time of even a single second. 
<br />

<br />
4) Complete Heal - It should never have existed. The developer who designed this spell had a very different perspective on the future game then the current developers. An ability that will always be at maximum effectiveness is flawed.
<br />

<br />
5) Call of the Hero - Another spell that should never have existed. Any spell that allows characters to bypass content is essentiall nullifying a part of the game.
<br />

<br />
6) Summon Corpse - Like Call of the Hero, it shouldn't exist in it's current state. Players need to be able to summon their corpse, however, it should be limited to only certain areas ie. the zone in or safe point.
<br />

<br />
7) Snare - The one that slips under the radar. So many imbalances are created by allowing a class to change the run speed of a monster that it isn't funny. This spell alone is the reason why high level monsters can spontaneously summon a player to them.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
