				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think the problem with slow is the fact that fighting any XP mob without it becomes a major challenge, to anyone who has no form of slow, (even necros get an attack reducer although I dont believe it helps a lot, its better than we get). Without it, you're doing a lot more work and suffering a lot harder. Imagine the extra mana used by healers if slow wasnt applied. 
<br />

<br />
I certainly thing charm is also pretty overpowerful when for example a chanter can probably charm any XP mob's best friend and use it to beat the mob to death. Yes there are major potential drawbacks to the charm, but with chanter stun, rune, its possible to charm the thing again before getting majorly hurt, even when hasted.
<br />

<br />
I think it would be kinda interesting to see the mobs scaled so that slow wasnt required. Id love to see how the world would be considering it felt at 50 our pet was kinda on par with a mob who conned even to it, now things like PoP and GoD have mobs with 4 or 5x our pet, fully buffed up, and will cream through him well, as people say like a speedbump.
<br />

<br />
I wish there was a way to do what ifs with eq.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
